This paper deals with automated information extraction from unstructured text, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on cyber-security, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of structured data to label text and the implementation of a Maximum Entropy Model suggest that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
